==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water monitor
<hw>Wa"ter mon"i*tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A very
large lizard (<spn>Varanaus salvator</spn>) native of India. It
frequents the borders of streams and swims actively. It becomes five or
six feet long. Called also <altname>two-banded monitor</altname>, and
<altname>kabaragoya</altname>. The name is also applied to other aquatic
monitors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water monkey</ent>⟦br⟧
